column2: A light- breezy + mostly sunny day.

column1: New visitors on the lake.  For the first time ever- spotted otters on the lake.  Mom and two pups were have a pleasant afternoon in the southwest corner of the lake.

column2: Mostly sunny with mild breeze.  Temp around 70.

column1: Loons eggs still has not hatched.  Great Blue Heron fishing on the shoreline. No otters sighted today.

column1: Perfect lazy day by the lake. The loon family (2 adults and one chick) are happy floating the day away occasionally diving for a fish or two.

column2: Super sunny and hot day.  89 degrees with only slight breeze from the SW.
Sunny warm day after several cold and rain filled days.  Lake water level is the highest I've seen in the eight years I've been here.
Big rains over the last few day.
Mostly cloudy day. A warm 75 degrees with only a very slight breeze.

Sorry for the late start this year.  A combination of awful weather and some mechanical issues with my boat were the cause.  The spring and much of the summer have been very wet and below average cold.  Lake level is as high as I've seen in ten years here and and high as any of the 'old timers' can remember.  The drainage culvert has been flowing out since mid-April at an estimated 200+ gallons per minute- but the flow out has not kept up with the rain so the lake level has actually risen since the culvert was opened.
No rain for several days now- but lake level is still as high as ever in-spite of the drain culvert's steady out flow of water.
